						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab lying in the village tank.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōmēśvara I A.D. 1042-43.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalladēva</hi> and records a grant, the details of which are lost. The grant was made in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 964, Chitrabhānu, Sunday.</hi> The month and the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> are lost. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 964, Chitrabhānu</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1042-43.</hi></p>						

						<p><hi rend="italic">Agrahāra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Benatavura,</hi> (modern Bentūr, the findspot of the record), <hi rend="bold">Beḷvala</hi> and, a <hi rend="italic">Mahāsāmanta</hi> (name lost) are mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
